# Section Tag Typography

Section tags (labels above body copy) must use the **exact same font as the navigation** for visual consistency.

## Font Properties

Apply to `.section-tag`, `.page-tag`, `.case-section-label`, `.about-tag`, and any similar labels:

```css
font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
font-size: 15px;
font-weight: 400;
letter-spacing: 0.12em;
text-transform: uppercase;
color: var(--accent);
```

## Affected Classes

- `.section-tag` — index (Experience, Community, Say Hello), about (Say Hello)
- `.page-tag` — portfolio (Selected Work)
- `.case-section-label` — case studies (Challenge, Approach, Outcome, etc.)
- `.about-tag` — about page intro label

## When Body Copy Uses a Different Font

If body copy uses a different font (e.g. Manrope), ensure the tag selector is **more specific** than the body copy selector so it doesn't get overridden. Example:

```css
.about-text p.about-tag { /* tag: Cormorant */ }
.about-text p:not(.about-tag) { /* body: Manrope */ }
```
